Personal Data We Collect
When you use our Products and Services, we collect the following types of personal data in the following ways.
Information You Provide To Us
Communications With Us
We may collect information from you, such as your name, email address, phone number or mailing address, when you choose to request information about our Products and Services, register to receive Arccos Golf newsletters and other communications by email and/or SMS/MMS messages (commonly referred to as “text messages”), participate in promotions or loyalty programs that we may offer from time to time, request to receive support or otherwise communicate with us.
User Account Information
Some information is required to create an account on our Services, such as your name, username, email address (which will be your login ID), password, date of birth (which we use to verify your age), and payment information.
If you choose to register for an account using your social media or other third-party credentials (if applicable), you will be asked to allow Arccos Golf access to information accessible from such third-party site, such as your name, date of birth, profile picture, gender, networks, third-party site user ID, and other content and information.
Purchases and Subscriptions
If you purchase Products directly from Arccos Golf or register for our Services, you provide your payment information, including name, credit or debit card number, card expiration date, CVV code, and billing address.
Your credit or debit card information is processed by an e-commerce platform or payments processor and we do not collect, store or maintain this information. Those platforms or processors may retain this information in accordance with their own privacy policies and terms.
Additional Information
User Content:
You may choose to provide additional information such as your profile photo. For example, if you choose to complete your user profile, your first and last name (or fictitious names that you may provide) and username are included on your profile page and in search results. Your golf handicap is automatically included on your profile page. You may also post or share other content and information through the Services, such as data, images, comments, location information, and other information ("
User Content
"). You can modify and correct this information by logging into your account.
Other Information You May Share:
You may share information with us through features of the Services to help you find people you know and connect with other services. For example, you may choose to upload information from your contacts or to connect your Arccos Golf account to third-party services such as Facebook or Twitter. Arccos Golf will match the information you provide with the contact information provided by other users. When you connect your Arccos Golf account to other services, you may post your User Content to those services.
You may disconnect your Arccos Golf account from third-party services at any time. When you disconnect one of your third-party services from your Arccos Golf account, we will take reasonable steps to delete information obtained from that connection other than publicly-posted User Content.
Information You Share With Other Users And Services:
If you choose to share information from your account with others, we will collect personal data you provide about your contacts, such as name and email address. You may choose to share your Golf Data and related statistics and analytics with others, but only as permitted by, and using the facilities of, the Arccos Dashboard.
You also have the option to publicly share your profile information and other User Content with other users and third-party services. Publicly sharing this information is optional.
Usage, viewing, technical, and device data.
When you visit our App or Site, use our applications on third-party sites or platforms, open emails we send, or connect with our wireless Internet access services and other similar technologies, we may collect usage, viewing, technical and device data that may include information such as your browser or device type, unique device identifier, and IP address.
We may share this information with third parties as described below in the “Analytics and Advertising Services Provided by Others” section of this Privacy Policy and our “
Cookie Policy
.”
Information We Receive From Third Parties
Services:
If you choose to connect your account to another service, we may receive information from the other service. For example, if you connect to Facebook or Twitter, we may receive information from those services such as your name, profile picture, language, email address, and friend list. You can stop sharing the information from the other service with us by removing our access to that other service.
Other Users:
Other users may provide information about you when they choose to share information from their accounts with you, and we may collect your name, username, or email address.
Automatically Collected Information
Golf Data:
In connection with your use of Products and the App, the following Golf Data is collected:
Geolocation Data:
The App uses your mobile device to collect precise geolocation data from the Global Positioning System. We may also derive your approximate location from your IP address.
You must first enable location services in the App. You may disable location services within the App at any time. Disabling location services may impact or eliminate certain functionalities in the App and other Products and Services.
Camera:
We use your mobile device’s camera to pair your Arccos Golf club sensors to the App. You may choose to enable other uses of your camera in the App, if available.
Microphone:
We use your mobile device’s microphone to track your shot data. If you use your mobile device’s digital assistant to interact with the App, your microphone’s data will be sent by your device to the provider of that service. Arccos Golf does not receive that data. Arccos Golf does not use your mobile device’s microphone for any other purpose.
Other Sensors:
We may also collect Golf Data from other sensors on your mobile device, for example the accelerometer, gyroscope and barometer.
Log Data:
We collect log data about the browser and operating system you are using, the address of the external or internal page that referred you, your IP address at the time of account creation, and the IP address associated with the device running the App each time you sync. We also keep a log of the pages that you visit on the Services in association with your IP address. We may also collect information about your access times, pages viewed, search terms, mobile carrier, device type, device IDs, application IDs, and version of the App. We may also collect information on how you access and interact with the Services, such as email notifications and third-party services.
We collect this information to generate statistics about use of the Services and use the results to customize as well as improve the overall quality of the Services. In general, we either delete log data or remove any personal identifiers, such as your name, username, email address, or IP address, within 18 months of collection.
Cookies:
We use cookies and similar technologies for the purposes described above. For more information, please read our
Cookie Policy
.
Third-Party Products Or Services
Third parties may offer separate products and services through advertisements on our App or Site and through the Services that may be complementary to your use of our Products and Services, such as golf attire and equipment, training materials, or related products and services. If you choose to use these separate products or services, disclose information to the providers, or grant the third parties permission to collect information about you, their use of your information is governed by their privacy policies and not by the Arccos Golf Privacy Policy.
How We Use Personal Data
The following describes how we use the personal data that we collect.
Provide Our Products And Services
We use information we collect to provide you with our Products and Services. We use your Golf Data to track your performance and provide you (and if you choose, others) with Services. We may also use your information to administer your account, send push notifications when you are using the Services, send you text messages, and connect you with other people who may use the Services. We use information we collect to tailor our Services to you, including to assess your needs and determine suitable content and Services, and to provide content based upon your interests.
We may use information we collect to ship Products to you, notify you about changes to our Terms of Use or related policies, and to provide information about our Products and Services. We also use information we collect to respond to questions, concerns and customer service requests, and to send you promotional communications by email and/or text message.
We use information to customize content available on the Services and to improve the quality of advertisements that offer third-party products and services. We also use information we collect to tailor the promotional communications we send you. You can opt out of promotional communications through a link provided in the communication.
Maintain And Improve Our Products And Services
We use information we collect to conduct research and analysis relating to our Products and Services, and to improve the overall experience of all of our users. We also use the information to troubleshoot and protect against errors; perform data analysis and testing; conduct research and surveys; and develop new features and Services.
We may use aggregate, de-identified location or other data, alone or in the aggregate with information obtained from other sources, to help us improve our Products and Services or develop new products and Services, or to share and report statistics through the Services. For example, we may use Golf Data to determine and display the average drive length of App users on a given hole.
Promote Safety And Security
We use the information we collect for other legitimate purposes to promote the safety and security of our Products and Services, our users, and other parties. For example, we may use the information to authenticate users, facilitate secure payments, protect against fraud and abuse, respond to a legal request or claim, conduct audits, and enforce our terms and policies.
Grounds for processing
We only collect and use personal data where we have lawful grounds to do so. These include processing personal data to provide our Products and Services, for purposes of our legitimate interests or those of other parties, to fulfill our legal obligations, or based on consent.
How We Share Personal Data
We may share your information as described in this Privacy Policy or with your permission.
When You Agree Or Direct Us To Share
You may direct us to disclose your information to third parties. For instance, you may have the Services share your information with other users. You may also direct us to share your information in other ways, for example, when you give a third-party application access to your account. For example, if you connect your account to Facebook or Twitter, we may disclose your information to those applications.
Service Providers
We transfer information to our service providers who process it for us, based on our instructions, and in compliance with this Privacy Policy, applicable law, and appropriate confidentiality and security measures. These service providers provide us with services including customer support, information technology, payments, sales, marketing, data storage and analysis, research and surveys.
We may share the information we collect with companies that provide support services to us (such as printers, e-mail providers, marketing services, analytics providers, web hosting providers, call center/chat providers, sweepstakes vendors, payment processors, data enhancement services, fraud prevention providers or shipping services providers, including product vendors) or that help us market our products and services. These companies may need information about you in order to perform their functions. We limit information shared with service providers to what is necessary to fulfill the services.
Professional services providers such as golf coaches and club fitters that have created a special account to engage in Permitted Professional Use of the Dashboard have access to Arccos App users’ Golf Data and certain User Information.
Non-identifiable Or Aggregate Information
We may share non-identifiable or aggregate information with third parties for lawful purposes such as market research and targeted advertising.
Public Information
We may share or disclose your public information, including your public profile information such as your name, username and profile picture, as well as any other information on your profile that you choose to make public. Public information also includes content, such as data from your use of the Products, that you choose to share on or through the Services, as well as your interactions with content shared by others.
Legal Requirements
We may disclose information we collect when we believe disclosure is appropriate to comply with the law; to enforce or apply applicable terms and conditions and other agreements; to prevent, detect, or investigate illegal activity, fraud, or abuse; to facilitate the financing, securitization, insuring, sale, assignment, bankruptcy, or disposal of all or part of our business or assets; or to protect the rights, property or safety of our company, our customers and others.
Subsidiaries, Affiliates And Partners
We share the information we collect with Arccos Golf subsidiaries and affiliates, such as Arccos Golf UK. We also share information with business partners, such as retailers and manufacturers of golf equipment, with whom we may jointly offer our Products and Services, or whose products or services we believe may be of interest to you.
Business Transfers
In connection with the sale or transfer of some or all of our business assets, we may transfer personal information. We also may retain a copy of that information.
Access And Control Of Your Personal Data
We provide account settings and tools to access and control your personal data regardless of where you live. If you live in certain jurisdictions, you may also have legal rights with respect to your information.
You can access some of the information that we collect about you. If you are a currently-registered user, you may access or modify your personally-identifiable information at any time by signing into your account. You may access or modify your communications preferences by following the instructions included in any communications you receive. Administrative communications concerning the Services are provided to all registered users and considered to be a part of the Services.
You may modify or delete your information or User Content, subject to limitations, through your account. You can also permanently delete your Arccos Golf account by
contacting us.
We take reasonable steps to remove personally-identifiable information and other information associated with your account promptly after you delete your account. In certain circumstances, however, Arccos Golf may be unable to remove some of your information and User Content, such as information you post through the Services to other services or otherwise publicly share.
Depending on your location, you may have the right to file a complaint relating to our handling of your personal data with the data protection authority in your country. For example, users in the European Union may submit such requests to the data protection authorities in the country in which they live.
Data Retention
We keep your account information, such your name, email address, and password, for as long as your account is in existence because we need it to operate your account. In some cases, when you give us information for a feature of the Services, we delete the data after it is no longer needed for the feature. For instance, if you provide your contact list for finding friends on the Services, we will delete the list after it is used for adding contacts as friends. We keep other information, like your performance data, until you use your account settings or tools to delete the data or your account because we use this data to provide you with your personal statistics and other aspects of the Services. We also keep information about you and your use of the Services for as long as necessary for our legitimate business interests, for legal reasons, and to prevent harm.
Services Provided by Others
We work with partners who provide us with analytics and advertising services. This includes helping us understand how users interact with the Services, serving advertisements on our behalf across the internet, and measuring the performance of those advertisements. These companies may use cookies and similar technologies to collect information about your interactions with the Services and other websites and applications. The information collected by such tracking technologies may be combined with other information that our partners have access to, including your name, email address and physical address, so that we can send you materials, either electronically or by direct mail, that may be of interest to you.
Our analytics and advertising service partners may use cookies and other tracking technologies to collect information about your use of the App and/or Site, including content you have viewed. We may share your viewing information together with certain personal information with these and other third parties.
These third parties may use this information to help Arccos Golf deliver advertising on the App and/or Site and on other third party websites based on your browsing activity on the App and/or Site. Arccos Golf may further tailor the advertising on the App and/or Site and these other third party websites based on additional information to the extent known by Arccos Golf or these third parties. Two of the third parties that Arccos Golf works with are Google and Facebook. In addition to using the information it collects performing services for Arccos Golf, Google may also use such information as described in its privacy policy. To see how Google may use information collected through our use of the Google services on the App and/or Site visit
https://www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners.
Facebook may also use information that it has about you and that it collects performing services for Arccos Golf (which may be associated with personal information that Facebook has about you) as described in its privacy policy available at
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy.
We also work with third party ad networks to display advertising on our App and Site and on third party websites. Our ad network vendors use technologies to collect information about your activities on the App and/or Site and to provide you cookie-based targeted advertising based upon your browsing activity and your interests.
To learn more, please read our
Cookie Policy
. To opt out of sharing your information with these third parties, please see the section below on your Right To Withdraw Consent.
Children
Our Services are not directed to children under the age of 13 and Arccos Golf does not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe your child under the age of 13 has provided Arccos Golf with personal data without your consent, please
contact us.
If we become aware that a child under 13 (or under the age of 16 in certain jurisdictions) has provided us with personal data, Arccos Golf will take reasonable steps to delete the personal data as soon as possible and terminate the child's account.
How We Protect Your Information
We take reasonable measures to protect and secure your personal data against unauthorized access or disclosure. We cannot guarantee, however, that these security measures will protect your information from hackers or human error. We review our business practices periodically for compliance with policies and procedures governing the security of our information.
To register with the Services, you will be required to select a password to protect your account unless you choose to register your account using a third-party service (if applicable). You are responsible for maintaining the security of your login ID and password. If you believe that your login ID or password have been compromised you should immediately change your password. We are not responsible if someone else accesses your account through registration information they have obtained from you or through a violation by you of this Privacy Policy or our Terms of Use.
International Operations And Data Transfers
You agree that all personal information that we collect may be transferred, processed and stored anywhere in the world, including but not limited to, the United States, Canada, the European Union, in the cloud, on our servers, on the servers of our affiliates or on the servers of our service providers. Your personal information may be accessible to law enforcement or other authorities as described above. By providing information to Arccos Golf, you explicitly consent to the storage of your personal information in any of these locations.
European Privacy Disclosures
Data Controllers
Arccos Golf is the data controller for the personal data collected in connection with use of our Products and Services in the European Economic Area (the “
EEA
”), the United Kingdom and Switzerland.
Lawful Basis For The Processing Of Personal Data
For personal data subject to the General Data Protection Regulation (“
GDPR
”), we rely on several legal bases to process the data, including:
When you have given your consent, which you may withdraw at any time using your account settings and other tools or by contacting us;
When the processing is necessary to perform a contract with you, like the Terms of Use; and
Our legitimate business interests, such as in improving, personalizing, and developing our Products and Services, marketing new features or products that may be of interest, and promoting safety and security.
Further information about our processing of personal data can be found above in the section entitled How We Use Personal Data.
Data Subject Rights
If you are a resident of the European Union (the “
EU
”), you have rights that you can exercise under certain circumstances in relation to your personal data that we hold. These rights are to:
Request
access
to your personal data (commonly known as a “data subject access request”) and request certain information in relation to its processing;
Request
rectification
of your personal data;
Request the
erasure
of your personal data;
Request the
restriction
of processing of your personal data;
Object
to the processing of your personal data.
You also have the right to
receive
your personal data in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and to have us
transmit
your personal data to another controller, if you have provided your personal data to us, and if the processing is based on consent or is necessary for the performance of your agreement with Arccos Golf, and the processing is carried out by us by automated means, subject, however, to legal restrictions which may apply.
If you want to exercise one of these rights please
contact us
.
You also have the right to make a complaint at any time to the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO), the UK supervisory authority for data protection issues, or, as the case may be, any other competent supervisory authority of an EU member state. The EU Commission has a list here:
http://ec.europa.eu/justice/article-29/structure/data-protection-authorities/index_en.htm
Right to withdraw consent
If you have provided your consent to the collection, processing and transfer of your personal data, you have the right to fully or partly withdraw your consent. To withdraw your consent, please
contact us
as described below. Once we have received notification that you have withdrawn your consent, we will no longer process your information for the purpose(s) to which you originally consented unless there are compelling legitimate grounds for further processing which override your interests, rights and freedoms or for the establishment, exercise or defense of legal claims. In case we processed your personal data for direct marketing purposes, you have the right to object at any time, in which case we will no longer process your personal data for such marketing purposes.
Please note that, except as otherwise stated above, once we share your personal information with another company in the above circumstances, the information received by the other company is controlled by that company and becomes subject to its privacy practices.
Changes To This Policy
We may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time. The most current version, which you should periodically review, is always available
here
. If we make a change to our Privacy Policy that, in our sole discretion, is material, we will notify you via email to the email address registered with your account or, in appropriate circumstances, through the Services (e.g., notification upon accessing the App, Site, or other web-based services).
By continuing to access or use the Services after those changes become effective, you consent to the terms of the revised Privacy Policy.
How To Contact Us
If you have questions about this policy, or wish to exercise your privacy rights, please contact us at:
Email:
